I0331 10:37:49.688210    2006 conn_opt.go:55] jsonrpc2: --> request #50: conversation/chat/updateHistory: {"History":[{"entity":"USER","markdownText":"what else do i need to finish the docker build","chatSectionId":"0","ideContext":{"currentFile":{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.dockerignore","language":"plaintext","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CURRENTLY_OPEN","isUntitled":false},"remoteContexts":null,"remoteRepositories":[],"otherFiles":[{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/pg-types/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/dotenv/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/50d36fb6/Xcrs.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/50d36fb6/9bhK.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/base64-js/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.gemini/extensions/vertex/src/vertex/prompt_optimizer/docs/data_driven_optimize_tuning_guide.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/50d36fb6/1Y9T.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/@types/nodemailer/lib/mime-node/index.d.ts","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/50d36fb6/jeK3.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/csstype/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false}],"rules":null,"editableRegion":null,"recentUserActions":null,"chatSectionId":"0"},"id":"439fc033-b45c-4bfd-a2ee-6fe7bb133f22","agentMetadata":{"coderAgent":{"kind":""},"model":""}},{"traceId":"21cc2be2be5c43b8","entity":"SYSTEM","markdownText":"\u003e Gemini 2.5 generated this response due to high traffic on Gemini 3\n\nOf course! It looks like you've made a good start with your `.dockerignore` file. That's an important step to keep your Docker image small and secure by preventing unnecessary or sensitive files from being included.\n\nThe main thing you're missing to complete your Docker setup is a `Dockerfile`. This file contains the step-by-step instructions that Docker uses to build your application's image.\n\nBased on the files you have, it looks like you're working with a Node.js application that might have a build step (for frontend assets) and a server-side component. A great way to structure your `Dockerfile` for this kind of project is to use a multi-stage build. This technique helps create a smaller, more secure, and more efficient production image.\n\nHere is a `Dockerfile` that should be a great starting point for you. I'll create it in your project's root directory.\n\n### Create the Dockerfile\n\n```diff\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile\n@@ -0,0 +1,42 @@\n+#\n+# Stage 1: Build Stage\n+# This stage installs all dependencies (including devDependencies) and runs the build script.\n+#\n+FROM node:18-alpine AS builder\n+\n+WORKDIR /usr/src/app\n+\n+# Copy package.json and package-lock.json to leverage Docker cache\n+COPY package.json package-lock.json* ./\n+\n+# Install all dependencies\n+RUN npm ci\n+\n+# Copy the rest of your application's source code\n+COPY . .\n+\n+# Run the build script (e.g., for a React, Vue, or Angular frontend)\n+# If your project doesn't have a build step, you can remove this line.\n+RUN npm run build\n+\n+#\n+# Stage 2: Production Stage\n+# This stage creates the final, lean production image.\n+#\n+FROM node:18-alpine AS production\n+\n+WORKDIR /usr/src/app\n+\n+# Create and use a non-root user for better security\n+RUN addgroup -S appgroup \u0026\u0026 adduser -S appuser -G appgroup\n+USER appuser\n+\n+# Copy package files and install *only* production dependencies\n+COPY package.json package-lock.json* ./\n+RUN npm ci --omit=dev\n+\n+# Copy the built assets and necessary source code from the builder stage\n+COPY --from=builder /usr/src/app/dist ./dist\n+COPY --from=builder /usr/src/app/src ./src\n+\n+# Expose the port your application will run on\n+EXPOSE 3000\n+\n+# The command to start your application in production\n+CMD [\"node\", \"src/index.js\"] # Or whatever your entry point is\n\n```\n\n### What to do next\n\nWith the `Dockerfile` and `.dockerignore` in place, you're ready to build and run your image.\n\n1.  **Build the Image:** Open your terminal in the project root and run:\n    ```bash\n    docker build -t your-app-name .\n    ```\n    Replace `your-app-name` with a name for your image (e.g., `food-truck-app`).\n\n2.  **Handle Environment Variables:** Your `.dockerignore` file correctly excludes the `.env` file. This is best practice! You should provide configuration to your container at runtime, not build it into the image. You can do this with the `-e` flag.\n\n3.  **Run the Container:**\n    ```bash\n    docker run -p 3000:3000 -e \"DATABASE_URL=your_connection_string\" -e \"SECRET_KEY=your_secret\" your-app-name\n    ```\n    -   `-p 3000:3000` maps port 3000 on your machine to port 3000 in the container.\n    -   `-e \"...\"` passes environment variables into your container. You should pass all the variables your application needs from your `.env` file this way.\n\nYou may need to adjust the `Dockerfile` slightly to match your project's specific structure (e.g., change `src/index.js` to your server's entry point or adjust the `EXPOSE` port), but this should get you very close to a finished Docker build.\n\n\u003c!--\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]How can I use Docker Compose to manage my environment variables and run the container?[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]Explain the security benefits of using a non-root user in the Dockerfile.[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n--\u003e","chatSectionId":"0","ideContext":{"currentFile":{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.dockerignore","language":"plaintext","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CURRENTLY_OPEN","isUntitled":false},"remoteContexts":null,"remoteRepositories":[],"otherFiles":[{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/pg-types/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/dotenv/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/50d36fb6/Xcrs.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/50d36fb6/9bhK.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/base64-js/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.gemini/extensions/vertex/src/vertex/prompt_optimizer/docs/data_driven_optimize_tuning_guide.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/50d36fb6/1Y9T.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE","isUntitled":false},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/