e","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CURRENTLY_OPEN"},"remoteContexts":null,"remoteRepositories":[],"otherFiles":[{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/package.json","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CHAT_FILE_REFERENCED"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.dockerignore","language":"plaintext","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CHAT_FILE_REFERENCED"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.config/powershell/Microsoft.PowerShell_profile.ps1","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/buffer/package.json","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/build.yml","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/48b8dbe5/n3wb.yml","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/56ee5218/R9vE.yml","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/readable-stream/lib/_stream_writable.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/stream-browserify/node_modules/readable-stream/lib/_stream_writable.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/readable-stream/lib/_stream_readable.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/stream-browserify/node_modules/readable-stream/lib/_stream_readable.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/pg-types/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"}],"rules":null,"editableRegion":null,"recentUserActions":null,"chatSectionId":"1"},"id":"bb9b7c7c-63e6-4685-9c2e-da18d343481c","agentMetadata":{"coderAgent":{"kind":""},"model":""}},{"traceId":"a1ee6c88bf68f33c","entity":"SYSTEM","markdownText":"\u003e Gemini 2.5 generated this response due to high traffic on Gemini 3\n\nOf course. It's frustrating when a build fails with a cryptic error code. You've run into a couple of common Docker \"gotchas,\" and I can certainly help you fix them.\n\nThe `exit code: 243` from `npm` is almost always a permissions error. The `JSONArgsRecommended` warning is also a good practice to follow. Let's fix both.\n\n### The Problem\n\n1.  **Permissions Error (`exit code: 243`):** In the previous `Dockerfile`, we switched to the non-root `appuser`. Then, as `appuser`, we tried to run `npm ci --omit=dev`. This command needs to create a `node_modules` directory inside `/usr/src/app`, but the `appuser` doesn't have permission to write there (it's owned by `root`). This caused the build to fail.\n\n2.  **CMD Warning:** The warning you saw is because Docker recommends using the JSON array \"exec\" format for `CMD` and `RUN` instructions. While the previous version used this format, the comment at the end of the line can sometimes cause issues with Docker's parser.\n\n### The Solution\n\nThe fix is to adjust the order of operations in the `production` stage. We will perform all the file copying and `npm` installation steps as `root`, and then, as a final step before execution, change the ownership of all the files to `appuser` and switch to that user. This is a secure and common pattern.\n\nHere are the necessary changes for your `Dockerfile`:\n\n```diff\n--- a/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile\n+++ b/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile\n@@ -27,20 +27,21 @@\n # Create and use a non-root user for better security\n RUN addgroup -S appgroup \u0026\u0026 adduser -S appuser -G appgroup\n-USER appuser\n \n # Copy package files and install *only* production dependencies\n+# We'll do this as root, which is fine for a build step.\n COPY package.json package-lock.json* ./\n RUN npm ci --omit=dev\n \n # Copy the built assets and necessary source code from the builder stage\n COPY --from=builder /usr/src/app/dist ./dist\n COPY --from=builder /usr/src/app/src ./src\n \n+# Now, change ownership of all application files to the non-root user\n+RUN chown -R appuser:appgroup /usr/src/app\n+\n+# Switch to the non-root user for execution\n+USER appuser\n+\n # Expose the port your application will run on\n EXPOSE 3000\n \n # The command to start your application in production\n-CMD [\"node\", \"src/index.js\"] # Or whatever your entry point is\n+CMD [\"node\", \"src/index.js\"]\n\n```\n\nWith these changes, your `docker build` command should complete successfully without any errors or warnings. You can now build and run your container as before.\n\n\u003c!--\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]How can I use Docker Compose to manage my environment variables and run the container?[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]Explain the security benefits of using a non-root user in the Dockerfile.[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n--\u003e","chatSectionId":"1","promptCitations":[{"startIndex":1522,"endIndex":1710,"filepath":"/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile","citationText":"Create and use a non-root user for better security\n RUN addgroup -S appgroup \u0026\u0026 adduser -S appuser -G appgroup\n-USER appuser\n \n # Copy package files and install *only* production dependenc"},{"startIndex":1773,"endIndex":1998,"filepath":"/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile","citationText":"COPY package.json package-lock.json* ./\n RUN npm ci --omit=dev\n \n # Copy the built assets and necessary source code from the builder stage\n COPY --from=builder /usr/src/app/dist ./dist\n COPY --from=builder /usr/src/app/src ./"},{"startIndex":2185,"endIndex":2363,"filepath":"/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile","citationText":"Expose the port your application will run on\n EXPOSE 3000\n \n # The command to start your application in production\n-CMD [\"node\", \"src/index.js\"] # Or whatever your entry point is"}],"ideContext":{"currentFile":{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile","language":"dockerfile","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CURRENTLY_OPEN"},"remoteContexts":null,"remoteRepositories":[],"otherFiles":[{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/package.json","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CHAT_FILE_REFERENCED"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.dockerignore","language":"plaintext","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CHAT_FILE_REFERENCED"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.config/powershell/Microsoft.PowerShell_profile.ps1","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/buffer/package.json","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/build.yml","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/48b8dbe5/n3wb.yml","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/56ee5218/R9vE.yml","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/readable-stream/lib/_stream_writable.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/stream-browserify/node_modules/readable-stream/lib/_stream_writable.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/readable-stream/lib/_stream_readable.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/stream-browserify/node_modules/readable-stream/lib/_stream_readable.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.cache/typescript/5.9/node_modules/pg-types/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"}],"rules":null,"editableRegion":null,"recentUserActions":null,"chatSectionId":"1"},"openFileUri":"file:///home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile","ragStatus":"RAG_NOT_FOUND","timeToFirstToken":"364","agentProcessingDetails":{},"workspaceChange":{"files":[{"filePath":"/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile","newText":"#\n# Stage 1: Build Stage\n# This stage installs all dependencies (including devDependencies) and runs the build script.\n#\nFROM node:18-alpine AS builder\n\nWORKDIR /usr/src/app\n\n# Copy package.json and package-lock.json to leverage Docker cache\nCOPY package.json package-lock.json* ./\n\n# Install all dependencies\nRUN npm ci\n\n# Copy the rest of your application's source code\nCOPY . .\n\n# Run the build script (e.g., for a React, Vue, or Angular frontend)\n# If your project doesn't have a build step, you can remove this line.\nRUN npm run build\n\n#\n# Stage 2: Production Stage\n# This stage creates the final, lean production image.\n#\nFROM node:18-alpine AS production\n\nWORKDIR /usr/src/app\n\n# Create and use a non-root user for better security\nRUN addgroup -S appgroup \u0026\u0026 adduser -S appuser -G appgroup\n\n# Copy package files and install *only* production dependencies\n# We'll do this as root, which is fine for a build step.\nCOPY package.json package-lock.json* ./\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\n\n# Copy the built assets and necessary source code from the builder stage\nCOPY --from=builder /usr/src/app/dist ./dist\nCOPY --from=builder /usr/src/app/src ./src\n\n# Now, change ownership of all application files to the non-root user\nRUN chown -R appuser:appgroup /usr/src/app\n\n# Switch to the non-root user for execution\nUSER appuser\n\n# Expose the port your application will run on\nEXPOSE 3000\n\n# The command to start your application in production\nCMD [\"node\", \"src/index.js\"]","promptCitations":[{"startIndex":919,"