:"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/mkdirp/readme.markdown","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/48b8dbe5/n3wb.yml","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/build.yml","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"}],"rules":null,"editableRegion":null,"recentUserActions":null,"chatSectionId":"2"},"agentMetadata":{"coderAgent":{"kind":""},"model":""}},{"traceId":"a85879a097e69df7","entity":"SYSTEM","markdownText":"Docker Compose is perfect for this. Instead of typing out long `docker run` commands with multiple `-e` flags for every environment variable, you can define your entire setup in a single YAML file. \n\nCompose allows you to seamlessly pass your `.env` file directly into the container, which keeps your commands clean and your secrets secure.\n\nHere is how you can set up a `docker-compose.yml` file in your project root:\n\n```diff\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/home/perrymckay1/docker-compose.yml\n@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@\n+version: '3.8'\n+\n+services:\n+  app:\n+    build: .\n+    container_name: food-truck-app\n+    ports:\n+      - \"3000:3000\"\n+    # This directive tells Docker Compose to automatically load \n+    # all variables from your .env file into the container.\n+    env_file:\n+      - .env\n```\n\n### How to use it:\n\n1. **Create your `.env` file** (if you haven't already) in the same directory (`/home/perrymckay1/`). Make sure it contains your required variables, like:\n   ```ini\n   DATABASE_URL=your_connection_string\n   SECRET_KEY=your_secret\n   ```\n\n2. **Start your application:**\n   Open your terminal in the project root and run:\n   ```bash\n   docker compose up -d\n   ```\n   *Note: The `-d` flag runs the container in \"detached\" mode (in the background) so you can keep using your terminal.*\n\n3. **Check the logs:**\n   If you want to see the output from your Node.js application to ensure it started correctly, you can run:\n   ```bash\n   docker compose logs -f\n   ```\n\n4. **Stop your application:**\n   When you're done, you can stop and remove the container with a single command:\n   ```bash\n   docker compose down\n   ```\n\nThis approach makes local development and managing your container configuration vastly easier!\n\n\u003c!--\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]How do I add a PostgreSQL database service to my docker-compose.yml file?[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n[PROMPT_SUGGESTION]What is the difference between env_file and environment in docker-compose.yml?[/PROMPT_SUGGESTION]\n--\u003e","chatSectionId":"2","ideContext":{"currentFile":{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/Dockerfile","language":"dockerfile","selection":{"start":797,"end":797},"includedReason":"CURRENTLY_OPEN"},"remoteContexts":null,"remoteRepositories":[],"otherFiles":[{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.dockerignore","language":"plaintext","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"CHAT_FILE_REFERENCED"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/dotenv/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/dotenv/README-es.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/-46867d3a/IBbT.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.codeoss/data/User/History/-46867d3a/2d3P.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/db.js","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/.config/powershell/Microsoft.PowerShell_profile.ps1","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedReason":"RELATED_FILE"},{"path":"/home/perrymckay1/node_modules/dotenv/README.md","language":"","selection":{"start":0,"end":0},"includedRe