ect file ownership to prevent the permission-denied error. Thus, the `COPY` commands must use the `--chown` flag, which I already planned to do, to ensure that the `appuser` owns the files and directories. Additionally, to avoid the JSON warning, I will remove the comment in the `CMD` instruction, completing the solution.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Root Cause**\n\nI'm now fully focused on the permission problem. The `exit code: 243` stems from `appuser` lacking write access within `/usr/src/app` after `WORKDIR` and `USER` changes, which are done before the files are copied. Specifically, `npm ci` cannot create `/usr/src/app/node_modules`. I'll implement `--chown` on `COPY` commands and ensure `appuser` owns the destination directory.\n\n\n**Reassessing Ownership and COPY**\n\nI'm now fully focused on debugging the build failures. The `appuser` cannot write to `/usr/src/app`. The `COPY` commands are the key, and I must use the `--chown` flag to ensure ownership. The `WORKDIR` must be owned by the `appuser` before the `npm ci` command runs; I'm exploring setting this ownership before switching users. I also need to make sure the `CMD` format is correct.\n\n\n**Addressing Build Failure Causes**\n\nI'm now fully focused on debugging the permissions problems, again. `appuser` cannot write to `/usr/src/app` after `WORKDIR` and `USER`. The files must be copied before switching users, but then the user needs to own those files. Using `--chown` on `COPY` is key. Then `npm ci` should succeed, since `appuser` owns the copied files and can create the `node_modules` directory.\n\n\n**Addressing Build Failure Causes**\n\nI'm now fully focused on debugging the permission issues, again. `appuser` cannot write to `/usr/src/app` after `WORKDIR` and `USER`. The files must be copied before switching users, but then the user needs to own those files. Using `--chown` on `COPY` is key. Then `npm ci` should succeed, since `appuser` owns the copied files and can create the `node_modules` director